HEADWORD: Ciliated
<hw>Cil"i*a`ted</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <def>Provided with, or surrounded
by, cilia; <as>as, a <ex>ciliate</ex> leaf</as>; endowed with vibratory
motion; <as>as, the <ex>ciliated</ex> epithelium of the
windpipe</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

